INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('1142', '1', '2014-03-13 05:00:12', '2014-03-13 05:00:12', 'In New York, DWI and DUI mean the same thing  drunk driving.whether youre in upstate or in the NYC metro area.\r\n\r\nAnd if youve been arrested and charged with DWI in New York. you have legal issues that will require smart and professional legal representation.\r\n\r\n<strong>New York DWI Penalties</strong>\r\n\r\nNew York law states that drivers that are stopped and arrested  <strong>the first time</strong>  can:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lose their drivers license for as long as six months;</li>\r\n	<li>Have to pay up to $1,000 in fines;</li>\r\n	<li>Spend up to one year in jail, and;</li>\r\n	<li>Be required to participate in a Drinking Driver Program (DDP), and;</li>\r\n	<li>Have to install and maintain an ignition interlock on any vehicle owned and operated by such driver for at least 6 months.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThose are serious issues. Even worse though, if youre found guilty of DWI, youll end up with a criminal record  which many times will cost you your job.\r\n\r\nThe only worse penalties are handed out to those that have a prior DWI conviction in the past 10 years. These arrests fall under New York Felony DWI DUI Penalties.\r\n\r\nOther issues that can have a major impact on whether youre convicted for DUI in New York, is whether breath, blood, or urine testing was done after the arrest  and were the results over the legal limit? If they were, thats were an experienced NY DWI attorney can make all the difference in the world.\r\n\r\nWeve put together much more detailed information about New York DWI testing and specific legal defenses we utilize in court at our New York DWI Testing and legal defense pages. Why not take a minute or two and get your questions answered about blood tests, urine tests and breath tests.\r\n\r\n<strong>Driving Privileges. The Most Important Issue For Many Of Our Clients</strong>\r\n\r\nOver the years, theres one thing weve learned  for most of our clients, being able to drive as soon as possible after an arrest for DWI in New York is extremely important.\r\n\r\nIn this state, theres no way around the law  when you are arrested and charged with DWI, and you refused to take a chemical test to determine your Blood Alcohol Content (BAC) your license is suspended right there at your arraignment.\r\n\r\nYour drivers license can then be revoked for at least one year after a hearing by the Department of Motor Vehicles.\r\n\r\nAgain, for this type of situation, it really is on your best interest to get the very best DUI attorney you can find.\r\n\r\n<strong>How We Can Help</strong>\r\n\r\nFacing a DWI charge is stressful. We promise to help you through the entire process, resolve any concerns you have, and answer all your questions. It is our duty to provide you with expert advice, guide you through the legal process, and represent you in the courtroom.\r\n\r\nEarlier on this page, I said you were going to need smart and professional legal representation. Wed like to be the New York DWI attorneys you call for that help.\r\n\r\nWhy not pick up the phone and call us for a FREE consultation. Were available 24 hours a day, 365 days a year.\r\n\r\nIn the <strong>NYC area and Long Island</strong>, call us at 212 683 5912.\r\nFor <strong>WNY &amp; Upstate NY</strong>, call 1 800 879 6410.\r\nIf the call is <strong>long distance</strong>, or you <strong>live elsewhere in the state</strong>, call us for free at 1 800 879 6410.\r\n\r\nWe wont pressure you  well just answer your questions.\r\n\r\nIf we work together to solve your legal problem. great. If not, thats okay too.\r\n\r\nWhy not put former prosecutors to work for you on your DWI arrest. We have a very strong track record of success throughout the State of New York, and we can certainly help with your DWI in New York  <strong>regardless of where you live.</strong>', 'New York DWI Overview', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'dwi-defense', '', '', '2014-03-18 06:00:12', '2014-03-18 06:00:12', '', '0', 'http://carlspector.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?page_id=1142', '0', 'page', '', '0');
