INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('1212', '1', '2014-03-18 06:21:56', '2014-03-18 06:21:56', '<h3>15 Very Good Reasons You Need The Best DWI  DUI Defense Attorneys You Can Find</h3>\r\n<strong>Details on New York DWI DUI Penalties</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you are convicted in <strong> NY for DWI / DUI</strong>, the first conviction can result in the following potential sentences:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>You may be sentenced to a maximum of one year in jail;</li>\r\n	<li>A minimum six-month drivers license suspension and;</li>\r\n	<li>Be required to install and maintain an ignition interlock device at your expense and;</li>\r\n	<li>Be ordered to pay mandatory fines, ranging from $500 to $1,000.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIf you are convicted in New York of a second DWI / DUI the second conviction will result in the following potential sentences:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>If the second DWI / DUI conviction is with in ten years of the first, your case may be enhanced and prosecuted as a felony in Supreme Court. You would then be facing enhanced penalties of a maximum of four years in prison, and;</li>\r\n	<li>If the second DWI / DUI is with in five years of the first, you may be sentenced to five days of mandatory jail or 30 days community service and/or;</li>\r\n	<li>Your drivers license will be revoked for a minimum of one year, and;</li>\r\n	<li>You will be required to install and maintain an ignition interlock device at your expense, and;</li>\r\n	<li>Be ordered to pay fines ranging from $1,000 to $5,000.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIf you are facing a third DWI / DUI offense in New York you are facing the following penalties:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Up to seven years in jail;</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum revocation of drivers license for one year;</li>\r\n	<li>If third conviction is within five years of the prior, minimum of 10 days jail, or sixty days of community service;</li>\r\n	<li>You will be required to install and maintain an ignition interlock device at your expense, and;</li>\r\n	<li>Mandatory alcohol evaluation;</li>\r\n	<li>Be ordered to pay fines ranging from $2,000 to $10,000.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nWhether its your first New York DWI / DUI, or youve been arrested on suspicion of DWI more than once, you need first-rate help. We urge you to call for a no obligation consultation.\r\n\r\nThe attorneys with www.newyorkdui.com have significant experience handling DWI matters and will use their knowledge of the law and New York prosecution methods to get the best possible result for your DWI or NY DWAI case.\r\n\r\nFor some of the most experienced DWI representation in New York, give us a call. We will not pressure you. We will not play any games. Well answer your questions  and ask you a few as well. And if you want us to help.we will.\r\nWere available 24 hours a day, 365 days a year.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In the <strong>NYC area and Long Island</strong>, call us at 212 683 5912.</li>\r\n	<li>For <strong>WNY &amp; Upstate NY</strong>, call 1 800 879 6410.</li>\r\n	<li>If the call is l<strong>ong distance, or you live elsewhere in New York</strong>, call us for free at 1 800 879 6410.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'New York DWI DUI Penalties', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-york-dwi-dui-penalties', '', '', '2014-03-18 06:22:55', '2014-03-18 06:22:55', '', '0', 'http://carlspector.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?page_id=1212', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('1213', '1', '2014-03-18 06:22:55', '2014-03-18 06:22:55', 'In New York, felony DWI / DUI charges generally happen under the following three circumstances:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>When the defendant has a previous DWI / DUI conviction within the past 10 years. While there are other circumstances that can lead to felony charges involving a DWI / DUI, this is the most common.</li>\r\n	<li>Where the DWI / DUI itself is a misdemeanor but the driver is charged with some other felony, like vehicular manslaughter if someone is killed.</li>\r\n	<li>It is now a class E felony to drive while intoxicated with a child 15 years of age or younger in the car. In addition, if the defendant is the parent, legal guardian, or custodian of the child in the vehicle, the police MUST file a report with Child Protective Services (CPS).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nFelony DWI in New York is much more serious than Misdemeanor DWI, and includes the possibility of state prison time. In New Yorks court system, these more serious criminal cases are mostly handled in the higher level courts  Misdemeanors stay in the Criminal Courts, while most of the substantive work in a felony is done in the Supreme Court.\r\n\r\nFelony prosecutors tend to be more experienced and more thorough than misdemeanor court prosecutors. They also have fewer cases so they can devote more time to each case. Bottom line.you might want to get the most experienced help you can find.\r\n\r\nIf you have been charged with Felony DWI/DUI in NY, we urge you to call for a no obligation consultation.\r\n\r\nThe attorneys with www.newyorkdui.com have handled numerous felony DWI / DUI cases in the New York Supreme Court system. We can defend, advise and counsel you from beginning to end in order to arrive at a satisfactory result of your case.\r\n\r\nFor some of the most experienced DWI/DUI representation in New York, give us a call. We will not pressure you. We will not play any games. Well answer your questions  and ask you a few as well. And if you want us to help.we will.\r\n\r\nIn the <strong>NYC area and Long Island</strong>, call us at 212 683 5912.\r\n\r\nFor <strong>WNY &amp; Upstate NY</strong>, call 1 800 879 6410.\r\n\r\nIf the call is <strong>long distance</strong>, or you <strong>live elsewhere in the state</strong>, call us for free at 1 800 879 6410.', 'New York Felony DWI DUI Penalties', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-york-felony-dwi-dui-penalties', '', '', '2014-03-18 06:22:55', '2014-03-18 06:22:55', '', '0', 'http://carlspector.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?page_id=1213', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('1214', '1', '2014-03-18 06:23:51', '2014-03-18 06:23:51', 'After your arrest for a DWI / DUI in New York, your drivers license will be administratively suspended at your arraignment and remain suspended until the end of your case.\r\n\r\nIf you are an out of state driver, your privileges to drive in New York will be suspended.\r\n\r\nBut. state law does provide you an opportunity to try to get a hardship drivers license in New York while your case is pending to drive to and from work. if a court is satisfied that you are eligible.\r\n\r\nThe factors that the court will consider are as follows:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>You must not have refused to take a chemical test;</li>\r\n	<li>You must not have had a previous DWI conviction within the last five years,;</li>\r\n	<li>You must testify at the hardship hearing that with out your drivers license you would suffer extreme hardship and that there is no viable alternative means of getting to work other than driving yourself, you may have to provide documentation to support your hardship claims;</li>\r\n	<li>You must have a witness testify who supports and confirms your hardship claims;</li>\r\n	<li>Additional witnesses must confirm that there are no family members, friends or coworkers that could drive you to work.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAnd a talented DUI attorney can assist you in getting your hardship license.\r\n\r\nIf you need driving privileges as soon as possible, we are there to assist you and help present your claim to the court for a hardship license.\r\n\r\nIf you have been charged with DWI/DUI anywhere in NY., we urge you to call for a no obligation consultation and ask questions about a NY DWI hardship license.\r\n\r\nWe have significant experience handling these matters and will use our knowledge of the law and New York courts to try and get your driving privileges restored as soon as possible.\r\n\r\nFor some of the most experienced DWI/DUI representation in New York, give us a call. We will 