INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('1221', '1', '2014-03-18 06:26:50', '2014-03-18 06:26:50', 'Any driver convicted of misdemeanor or felony drunk driving charges in NY  even first-time offenders  are required to install and maintain ignition interlock devices at their own expense on any vehicles they own or operate  for a minimum of six months.\r\n\r\nThe device is connected to a motor vehicle ignition system and measures the alcohol content of the operators breath. As a result, the vehicle cannot be started until the driver provides an acceptable sample breath.\r\n\r\nFor an Aggravated-DWI offense in New York, or any repeat alcohol or drug offense within five years, a judge is required to order the system installed on each vehicle owned or operated by the motorist during both the revocation period and any probation period that follows.\r\n\r\n<strong>How much does the Ignition Interlock Device cost?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe cost of the Ignition Interlock Device depends on the vendor and the level of ignition interlock service. Generally it costs approximately $100 for installation and a monthly fee of $100. And youll get no help in paying for this. The individual that is convicted of DWI in New York has to pay to pay all the fees associated with installing and maintaining these devices.\r\n\r\nThis cost, significant insurance rate increases, and impact on your current job and future employment opportunities, <strong>is the reason we work hard to try and get your DWI / DUI charges reduced or dismissed. </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Some Good News</strong>\r\n\r\nWhile using the interlock device, you may be eligible to hold a conditional license\r\n\r\nBut keep this in mind  your license will be revoked if you fail to comply with the courts terms, or you are convicted of any traffic offense other than parking, stopping or standing.\r\n\r\nIf youve been arrested for DWI anywhere in the state of New York  <strong>and need driving privileges</strong>  we urge you to call for a no obligation consultation.\r\n\r\nThe attorneys with New York DUI have significant experience handling DWI license suspensions and will use their knowledge of the law to get the best possible result for you.\r\n\r\nFor some of the most experienced DWI/DUI representation in New York, give us a call. <strong>We will not pressure you. We will not play any games.</strong> Well answer your questions  and ask you a few as well. And if you want us to help.we will.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In the <strong>NYC area and Long Island</strong>, call us at 212 683 5912.</li>\r\n	<li>For <strong>WNY &amp; Upstate NY</strong>, call 1 800 879 6410.</li>\r\n	<li>If the call is l<strong>ong distance, or you live elsewhere in New York</strong>, call us for free at 1 800 879 6410.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'New York DWI  DUI Ignition Interlock Device', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-york-dwi-dui-ignition-interlock-device', '', '', '2014-03-18 06:26:50', '2014-03-18 06:26:50', '', '0', 'http://carlspector.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?page_id=1221', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('1222', '1', '2014-03-18 06:27:30', '2014-03-18 06:27:30', 'Compared to other drivers, every driver holding a Commercial Driver License (Class A, B, or C) is <strong>held to stricter Blood Alcohol Content (BAC) standards</strong>, and faces tougher penalties, while operating a vehicle that requires a CDL license.\r\n\r\nThe attorneys with New York DUI understand that a conviction on a DWI / DWAI or DUI with a CDL can have devastating effects on your career and family.\r\n\r\nWe will employ all of our considerable knowledge, experience and skill to get the best possible result for you in this trying and stressful time.\r\n\r\nA single conviction for DWI, DWAI, DUI or having a .04 percent or higher BAC <strong>requires a minimum 1-year revocation of the drivers license (3 years, if driving a vehicle that requires hazardous materials placards)</strong>.\r\n\r\nA second conviction within the drivers lifetime results in permanent revocation, with a possible waiver after 10 years.\r\n\r\nA third conviction results in a permanent revocation without any possibility of ever getting it back. Drivers who hold a commercial license should review the Commercial Drivers Manual (CDL-10), available at motor vehicle offices, for additional information about penalties that apply to them.\r\n\r\n<strong>If you have a CDL, all it can take is one beer  and your career can be ruined.</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you find yourself facing a DWI / DUI charge, we urge you to call for a no obligation consultation. The attorneys with www.newyorkdui.com have significant experience handling CDL matters and can navigate through these difficult cases to get the best possible result for your DWI case.\r\n\r\nFor some of the most experienced CDL DWI/DUI representation in New York , give us a call. We will not pressure you. We will not play any games. Well answer your questions  and ask you a few as well. And if you want us to help.we will.\r\n\r\nIn the <strong>NYC area and Long Island</strong>, call us at 212 683 5912.\r\nFor <strong>WNY &amp; Upstate NY</strong>, call 1 800 879 6410.\r\nIf the call is <strong>long distance</strong>, or you <strong>live elsewhere in state</strong>, call us for free at 1 800 879 6410.', 'New York DWI / DWAI / DUI With Commercial Drivers License (CDL)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-york-dwi-dwai-dui-with-commercial-drivers-license-cdl', '', '', '2014-03-18 06:27:30', '2014-03-18 06:27:30', '', '0', 'http://carlspector.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?page_id=1222', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('1223', '1', '2014-03-18 06:28:37', '2014-03-18 06:28:37', 'It is illegal for a driver <strong>under age 21 to have consumed any alcohol</strong> in the state of New York. If you, or someone you know, has been charged with underage DWI / DUI in New York, please call the attorneys with www.newyorkdui.com.\r\n\r\nYou still have some of the same rights and defenses that any other person charged with DWI / DUI in New York has. These cases are defendable and winnable.\r\n\r\nAnd because of the age issue, this person has a lot more to lose. Besides future employment issues, college admission is at risk and even current enrollment in college can be affected.\r\n\r\n<strong>The Zero Tolerance Law In New York</strong>\r\n\r\nIf your BAC is .05 percent or greater, the police may charge you with driving while ability impaired (DWAI) or driving while intoxicated (DWI), and may prosecute your arrest in criminal court.\r\n\r\nA police officer may temporarily detain you to request or administer a chemical test to determine your Blood Alcohol Content (BAC).\r\n\r\nIf your BAC is .02 to .07 percent, you will be notified to appear at a DMV hearing. If the judges finding supports the charge, the penalty is a 6-month license suspension, a $125 civil penalty, and a $100 suspension termination fee.\r\n\r\nEach additional offense will result in your license being revoked for at least one year or until age 21, whichever is longer, plus a $125 civil penalty, and a $100 license re-application fee.\r\n\r\nA driver under 21 years old who refuses to take a chemical test under the Zero Tolerance Law is subject to a 1-year license revocation and a $125 civil penalty.\r\n\r\nUnder 21 arrests for drinking and driving in New York carry a heavy burden that negatively impact a young person for decades.\r\n\r\nIf you, or loved one under the age of 21 have been charged with DWI/DUI or DWAI anywhere in New York, we urge you to call for a no obligation consultation. The attorneys with New York DWI have significant experience handling these matters and can navigate through these difficult cases to get the best possible result for your case.\r\n\r\nFor some of the most experienced DWI/DUI representation in New York, give us a call. We will not pressure you. We will not play any games. Well answer your questions  and ask you a few as well. And if you want us to help.we will.\r\n\r\nWere available <strong>24 hours a day, 365 days a year</strong>.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In the <strong>NYC area and Long Island</strong>, call us at 212 683 5912.</li>\r\n	<li>For <strong>WNY &amp; Upstate NY</strong>, call 1 800 879 6410.</li>\r\n	<li>If the call is l<strong>ong distance, or you live elsewhere in New York</strong>, call us for free at 1 800 879 6410.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'New York DWI  DUI Under 21 Zero Tolerance Law', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-york-dwi-dui-under-21-zero-tolerance-law', '', '', '2014-03-18 06:28:37', '2014-03-18 06:28:37', '', '0', 'http://carlspector.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?page_id=1223', '0', 'page', '', '0');
